caption: Amazing Japanese food!
Fresh choices and friendly atmosphere with a great happy hour
Very good Japanese food with reasonable price close to tourist areas. We will come back again!!!

A great little shop for delicious sushi and a great happy hour menu! The staff is very friendly and attentive. A special shout out to Tomo, who took such good care of us and was so sweet and efficient. He always made sure we had everything we needed and always did it with a huge smile on his face-- no matter how busy they were. We truly appreciate the amazing customer service we got from him! The music and the general vibe of the place is a good compliment to the great food, as well! We will keep coming back each time we come back to waikiki.
Service is top notch, super friendly staff. Fried oysters were amazing. Sushi and udon was good. Tonkatsu was dry.
Amazing little spot for fresh sushi. Staff is friendly and the food was delicious. Get the fried octopus balls - you won’t regret it.
We visited and revisited this restaurant during our 2 week trip to Hawaii. The food and service was fantastic!
My husband said this is the best Japanese food he's eaten outside of Japan!
Very welcoming staff. Nice location, takes reservations, large sushi roll plates
Happy hour is the way to go at this hidden Waikiki gem.

Everything we ordered was fresh and authentic.  Yellow tail sashimi was  high quality.   Kushiyaki - skewers were all perfect  Is this restaurant owned by people from Chiba pref?   I am curious because I am!   #supportlocalbusinesses
Awesome service, fresh sushi, decent sake list and late night happy hour! This is my favorite local spot for sushi In Waikiki.
Friendly staff and great food for such a good price
Good eats!!
Delicious!!!!!!!!!!!

Service can be better...

A lot of restaurants have downsized their portions or quality of their food right now but NOT Chiba-ken! As usual, am never disappointed! We always order their over the top Tempura (yum) but are constantly blown away with everything else. Today was sashimi and sushi night.  Quality unsurpassed, artistically prepared, Oisihi!!!
My new local favorite! Food is always fresh and amazing! Very high quality service and food. I come here at least twice a week. 10/5 stars!

Sashimi is so fresh. Service is amazing. Such a great spot with great prices and quality food. Check it out!
This little spot really hit the spot! Delicious and affordable by Hawaii standards. The service was excellent and the fish was fresh.
I had the chicken katsu bento to go (the only option!) The chicken was surprisingly moist, even after waiting a half hour. I would definitely return for their other takeout options.
I got their bento, it's very big portion and very reasonable. And very tasty.
Outstanding service, food and price.  Try the pork belly in broth with soft boiled egg and any of the rolls.  The happy hour prices are very reasonable for the quality of food.
Good place for sushi. I tad bit overpriced. Specials at the end of the day. Overall great dishes
After 12 years in japan I think this place is almost like being back there. Service is exceptional and the food is exactly what you expect, delicious
Clean, quality, great variety. My fave on Oahu!
Happy hour is amazing. Service is perfect. Small outdoor seating that is ideal for the late night breeze.

In our week long vacation in Waikiki, this is the only place we had dinner twice. Very affordable, quick, quiet, and great service. Pork belly with the egg was so flavorful! Definitely recommend
This is an awesome Japanese restaurant with a sushi bar where the chefs make the sushi right in front if you. The food is delicious. Try the gyoza if you go.
Amazing hole in the wall Japanese restaurant. All the food is traditional Japanese style. Everything we tried we delicious, and we had a little of everything. 11/10 will never stop eating sushi.

Simply devine! Fresh and excellent quality. Staff is friendly. Off the beaten path it has seating inside and out. The shrimp tempura roll is to die for. Highly recommend you stop here!! They also have a "Happy Hour" menu from 9:30-close.

I've been to this restaurant twice before but for their late night happy hour menu. Always thought it was a good deal and liked the small menu. I decided to go again for New Year's Eve and the regular menu. I knew the service was hit or miss even when there are not many customers. My main problem after this dinner was more about the overall quality especially the sushi this day. The chirashi special is $37. It was not very special with not the best quality. The sushi rice was not great quality either. I also had a separate order of hamachi that was good. We always had to track down the help for service. No one ever checks on you. But then again I've noticed that at many restaurants in Hawaii. Overall I give this restaurant an acreage score. Go for the happy hour if you do.

Not being the most verbose sushi connoisser all I can say was it was damn good at a damn good price compared to wandering into downtown waikiki proper and getting the same thing at almost guaranteed lower quality and higher price. They have long table inside to accommodate big parties as well as an intimate patio and a long sushi bar rail. Biggest con I can see is parking. We were staying close by so we just walked there but if you were travelling by car you'd probably need to find a lot or maybe park near the marina/lagoon and walk up.
